    • Constructor Detail

      • Session

        public Session​(Course course,
               int sessionLength,
               DateTime startTime,
               Room room)
        Four-argument constructor. Session length, start time, end time and room are initialized by calling the set methods by those instance variables and doing certain checks that are part of the set methods in the class. The course is initialized in a regular manner.
        Parameters:
        course - one of the courses that should be assigned to the session.
        sessionLength - how long the session will take place.
        startTime - the time when the session should start.
        room - location, where the session will take place.

      • setRoom

        public void setRoom​(Room room)
        method is meant for setting a room for session. In the method it is checked if the room is chosen and otherwise it throws an exception. If the room is chosen it compares the capacity of the room and the amount of students that belong to the course and if it's true is initializes it, otherwise it will throw an exception.
        Parameters:
        room - the room that the session should be held in.

      • setStartTime

        public void setStartTime​(DateTime startTime)
        method is meant to set start time for a given session. It takes given time, when the session should start and checks if the hour and minute values are allowed. If the time value are allowed, a copy is taken of startTime. If the time value is not allowed, and exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        startTime - the copy of a time for when the session should start.

      • setEndTime

        public void setEndTime()
        method is meant to set end time for a given session. It checks the startTime of the session and the length of the session, and assigns a new endTime if the sessionLength is compatible with the startTime. If the sessionLength is not compatible with the startTime, an exception is thrown.

      • setSessionLength

        public void setSessionLength​(int sessionLength)
        method is meant to set session length. In the method using the if-statement length value is checked and if it's not 2, 3 or 4 it throws an exception.
        Parameters:
        sessionLength - how long the session will take place.
